    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning kinda yellow and pale compared to the top ones. what's probably going on with them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The yellowing leaves on your tomato plants, especially on the lower half, can be a sign of a few different issues. One possibility is that the plant is experiencing a phenomenon called \"lower leaf drop,\" where the lower leaves are simply being pushed out by the growing new leaves above them. This is a normal process, but if it's accompanied by other symptoms like yellowing or browning, it might be worth investigating further. It's also possible that the plant is experiencing nutrient deficiencies, such as nitrogen or iron, which can cause similar symptoms. \n\nHowever, it's also worth noting that this might be a case of \"giant\" leaf drop, where the plant is simply outgrowing its support system. You know, like when a young adult leaves the nest, it's a rite of passage, but in this case, it's the plant's way of adapting to its environment. \n\nTo address the issue, you can try adjusting your watering schedule, making sure the plant isn't getting too much or too little water. You can also consider fertilizing the plant with a balanced fertilizer to ensure it's getting all the necessary nutrients.",
